  "authors": [],
  "body": {
    "comment": "Summary\nYoroi DRep votes YES on the Info Action titled “Approve Cardano Foundation as New Managing Entity of Project Catalyst.” This decision is based on the need to maintain reliable execution of ongoing Catalyst commitments.\n\nRationale\n\n• Protecting delivery to funded teams\nActive projects under Funds 10–14 rely on predictable milestone validation and payouts. Any pause or uncertainty in administration directly affects teams already building, which should be avoided.\n\n• Administrative requirement, not expansion\nThis action fulfills a structural requirement under Catalyst Foundation Company statutes and does not introduce new funding or broaden Catalyst’s scope. It ensures previously approved commitments can be carried through.\n\n• Clear path to avoid unnecessary delays\nWith no alternative ready within the required timeline, approving a capable successor reduces coordination risk and prevents operational gaps.\n\nConclusion\n\nYoroi supports this proposal as a practical step to ensure that commitments already made through Catalyst are delivered in a predictable and timely manner. The priority at this stage is not to redefine Catalyst, but to ensure that ongoing work is not disrupted by administrative uncertainty. Questions around future structure, funding, and governance should be addressed separately, once continuity of current operations is secured."
  },
  "hashAlgorithm": "blake2b-256"
}